    <div class="baf-section">
      <div class="baf-section-head">
        <div class="baf-section-icon">📋</div>
        <div>
          <h2>Terms & Conditions</h2>
          <p>Governed by the laws of Western Australia — please read in full before submitting</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="baf-section-body">

        <div class="baf-tc-scroll" id="tc-scroll">

          <h4>1. Business Account — Scope & Purpose</h4>
          <p>These Terms govern the establishment and use of a Business Account ("Account") with EvoTech Digital (ABN 72 375 743 898) ("EvoTech"), a managed IT services and IT procurement provider based in Perth, Western Australia. A Business Account allows approved organisations ("Account Holder") to submit purchase requests for IT hardware, software, managed services, and related technology solutions.</p>

          <h4>2. Account Application & Approval</h4>
          <p>2.1 Submission of this application does not constitute automatic approval of a Business Account. EvoTech reserves the right to approve, decline, or conditionally approve any application at its sole discretion.</p>
          <p>2.2 EvoTech may conduct verification of the information provided, including contacting supplied trade references. By submitting this application, the Account Holder authorises EvoTech to make such enquiries.</p>
          <p>2.3 EvoTech will notify the applicant of its decision within 3–5 business days of receiving a complete application.</p>

          <h4>3. Purchase Requests & Orders</h4>
          <p>3.1 An approved Business Account enables the Account Holder to submit purchase requests. Each purchase request will be reviewed and quoted by EvoTech individually. A formal quote constitutes EvoTech's offer; the Account Holder's written acceptance constitutes a binding Order.</p>
          <p>3.2 EvoTech does not offer automatic credit lines. Payment terms for each Order are negotiated individually between EvoTech and the Account Holder prior to order confirmation.</p>
          <p>3.3 Standard payment terms for orders without a separately negotiated credit arrangement require a 50% advance deposit prior to procurement, with the remaining 50% balance payable on or before delivery.</p>

          <h4>4. Pricing & Quotations</h4>
          <p>4.1 All prices are quoted in Australian Dollars (AUD) inclusive of GST (10%) unless otherwise stated. Prices in quotes are valid for 14 days from the date of issue unless otherwise specified.</p>
          <p>4.2 EvoTech reserves the right to adjust pricing due to manufacturer price changes, currency fluctuations, or supply chain factors. Account Holders will be notified of material price changes before an Order is confirmed.</p>

          <h4>5. Title & Risk</h4>
          <p>Title to and ownership of goods remains with EvoTech until full payment of the Order value has been received in cleared funds, in accordance with the Personal Property Securities Act 2009 (Cth) ("PPSA"). Risk passes to the Account Holder upon delivery to the nominated address.</p>

          <h4>6. Delivery</h4>
          <p>6.1 Estimated delivery timeframes are provided in good faith and are not guaranteed. EvoTech accepts no liability for delays outside its reasonable control, including supplier and freight delays.</p>
          <p>6.2 Delivery is to the nominated address. The Account Holder is responsible for ensuring a suitable receiving person is available. Additional charges may apply for remote, restricted-access, or after-hours deliveries.</p>

          <h4>7. Warranties & Returns</h4>
          <p>7.1 Hardware products carry the manufacturer's warranty. EvoTech will assist in warranty claims as a courtesy service.</p>
          <p>7.2 Returns for change of mind are not accepted. Defective or incorrect goods must be notified in writing within 7 days of delivery. Goods must be returned in original packaging.</p>
          <p>7.3 Nothing in these Terms limits any rights the Account Holder may have under the Australian Consumer Law (ACL) (Schedule 2 of the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 (Cth)).</p>

          <h4>8. Australian Consumer Law</h4>
          <p>EvoTech complies with all applicable provisions of the Australian Consumer Law. Consumer guarantees apply and cannot be excluded where the ACL applies. EvoTech will not engage in misleading or deceptive conduct (s.18 ACL) or make false representations (s.29 ACL).</p>

          <h4>9. IT Procurement Standards</h4>
          <p>EvoTech aligns its procurement practices with the Digital Transformation Agency (DTA) ICT Procurement Framework and adheres to the Commonwealth Supplier Code of Conduct, including ethical supply chain practices and compliance with the Modern Slavery Act 2018 (Cth). Equipment is sourced in accordance with applicable Australian import, safety, and standards requirements.</p>

          <h4>10. Privacy</h4>
          <p>Information collected through this application is handled in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and EvoTech's Privacy Policy (evotech.au/policies/privacy-policy). Information is used for account administration, order processing, and business communications only and will not be sold or disclosed to third parties without consent, except as required by law.</p>

          <h4>11. Account Holder Obligations</h4>
          <p>The Account Holder agrees to: (a) keep account credentials secure; (b) notify EvoTech promptly of any change in contact, billing, or delivery details; (c) ensure purchase requests are submitted by authorised personnel only; and (d) not use the Account for unlawful purposes.</p>

          <h4>12. Account Suspension & Termination</h4>
          <p>EvoTech may suspend or terminate an Account with written notice if: the Account Holder fails to pay outstanding invoices; materially breaches these Terms; provides false information; or ceases to trade. Outstanding obligations survive termination.</p>

          <h4>13. Limitation of Liability</h4>
          <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law and subject to Clause 7.3, EvoTech's liability is limited to the value of the specific goods or services supplied. EvoTech is not liable for indirect, consequential, special, or economic loss, loss of data, loss of profit, or loss of business opportunity.</p>

          <h4>14. Overdue Payments</h4>
          <p>Overdue amounts accrue interest at 2% per month (compounding) from the due date, in accordance with the Civil Judgments Enforcement Act 2004 (WA). EvoTech reserves the right to suspend an Account pending payment of all overdue amounts.</p>

          <h4>15. Governing Law & Disputes</h4>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of Western Australia, Australia. The parties submit to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Western Australia. Disputes shall first be subject to good-faith negotiation (14 days), then mediation through the Law Society of Western Australia, before either party commences litigation.</p>

          <h4>16. Variations</h4>
          <p>EvoTech may update these Terms from time to time. Updated Terms will be published at evotech.au and apply to all Orders placed after the update date. Continued use of the Account constitutes acceptance of updated Terms.</p>

          <p style="margin-top:18px; font-style:italic; font-size:11px; color:#666;">Last updated March 2026. Prepared in accordance with the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 (Cth), Sale of Goods Act 1895 (WA), Personal Property Securities Act 2009 (Cth), Privacy Act 1988 (Cth), and the laws of Western Australia. This document does not constitute legal advice — seek qualified Australian legal counsel for advice specific to your circumstances.</p>

        </div><!-- /tc-scroll -->

